shared_text:
Wellbeing Connection
September 7 at 3:35 PM ¬∑

Join us this Tuesday (Sept. 8th) at 7 pm on Facebook Live as we explore the topics of loss and grief.‚Å£
‚Å£
We all experience loss in our lives - loss of a loved one or friend; and recently, we have experienced new types of loss brought on by the pandemic. ‚Å£
‚Å£
We also experience the variety of reactions that come with it. While loss often feels hurtful, it does not have to be harmful. So, let‚Äôs talk about it.
‚Å£
Laura Lewis, Licensed Professional Clinical Counselor and Supervisor (LPCC-S) will chat with us on how to use our cognitive and emotional strengths in coping with loss. ‚Å£
After Laura speaks, she will spend time answering questions. Email us at sharon@thewellbeingconnection.org or‚Ä¶ More

shared_text:
Wellbeing Connection
August 7 at 8:35 PM ¬∑

Join our community for an evening of healing and connection with Lori Bower. There has been a lot of loss and uncertainty these past few months and now it‚Äôs time to come together as a community and heal.

Lori will provide a path for us to restore and renew our energy. This practice is perfect for those who are feeling overwhelmed, sad, anxious or exhausted.

Urban Zen is a balance of gentle movements, breath practices, restorative postures, aromatherapy and guided meditation. You‚Äôll leave feeling calm, grounded, and relaxed. And, it‚Äôs appropriate for everyone - families, teens, adults, everyone!

Wednesday, August 12th | 6:30 PM to 8:00 PM

https://www.eventbrite.com/e/116132093217

This practice is brought to the community at no cost through a collaborative effort of Healthy New Albany & Wellbeing Connection.

#newalbanyohio #mynewalbany #wellbeingconnection #healthynewalbany #urbanzen #community #healing

Wellbeing Connection was live.
July 27 at 8:00 PM ¬∑

Meet Shawn. He runs Maryhaven - a behavioral health and addiction treatment center here in Central Ohio.

And we had a few questions for him.

üî∏Shawn, what trends are you seeing in substance abuse during the pandemic?
The pandemic has created an increased level of anxiety and isolation. As a result, substance abuse sales and overdoses have increased dramatically.

üî∏ How does someone know when it‚Äôs time to get help?
Typically, most individuals know when they need to seek help. For example, they are no longer able to sustain employment or relationships. They suffer from depression and use drugs and alcohol as a coping mechanism just to make it through the day.

Shawn is a New Albany resident and‚Ä¶

post_text:
Tough news from our Middle School Theatre Department. These students, staff and parent volunteers put so much work into it, but we understand the decision.

It is with great sadness that we make this announcement. Because of the risks of spreading COVID to both our performers and our audience, the fall production of Frozen, Jr. is cancelled. We want to acknowledge all the hours of rehearsals these students have spent creating the magic that would have been on stage. We would like to share with you our FROZEN family singing ‚ÄúFor the First Time in Forever‚Äù.

If you purchased tickets through CAPA, you can request a refund through them. We thank the community for their support and look forward to the time when we can perform for you again.

Sincerely, NAMS Theatre Department

https://youtu.be/gbOthIuEBdY #NAPride

post_text: Thank you Mrs. Gould as she produced this segment for our Black History Month program at New Albany Schools in 2019! It‚Äôs a poignant moment in our history and is as relevant today as ever and it‚Äôs beautiful. Thank you for our students for putting their heart into all of it. #NAPride
shared_text:
Melissa Gould
June 12 at 9:13 PM ¬∑

"Loving vs. Virginia" This is a piece I choreographed for the New Albany Black History program. These are MS and HS kids. Featuring Dominic Catrone and Clara Love with vocals by Edin Kebede.

‚ÄúTell the court I love my wife, and it is just unfair that I can‚Äôt live with her in Virginia.‚Äù

It was only a mere 53 years ago that interracial marriage became legal across our nation, thanks to Mildred and Richard Loving. Their courage paved the way for so many. #LovingDay

This video is for educational purposes only. It is not being monetized.

post_text: Proud of your work The Antidote Robotics! Great efforts to support our medical professionals, first responders and more... #NAPride
shared_text:
The Antidote Robotics
May 4 at 8:53 PM ¬∑

We are thankful for all the healthcare workers who are working hard to keep us all safe! And, we are extremely grateful to have the opportunity to play a small part in helping keep them comfortable.

As of today, we have donated 4000+ ear savers so far and we have requests for 1000+ more.

Thank you to all good samaritans who have donated at theantidoterobotics.com/donate. Because of you, over 4,000 ear savers have been printed & donated to hospitals, nurses, nursing homes, essential corporates, pharmacies, COTA, WPAFB. Ronald McDonald House, NA Transportation and several individual requests from #Ohio and beyond.
YOUR donations make a difference! Thank you!
New Albany-Plain Local Schools Mr.Michael Sawyers
Mr. Sloan Spalding Mr. Patrick J Gallaway
Dr. Gautham Chitragari, Mrs. Peg Carmany
Mr. Andy Moore and & Mr. and Mrs. Michael Carr
#InThisTogetherOhio
#StaySafeOhio
#NAPride

post_text: Happy to collaborate & share this space to keep our first responders safe! #NAPride
shared_text:
Plain Township Government
March 30 at 5:23 PM ¬∑

In response to the COVID-19 pandemic, the Plain Township Fire Department activated a substation, Station 122, to be housed at the NAPLS Bus Garage. With schools closed, the New Albany Plain Local School District has provided access to the facility that will staff a crew 24 hours a day.

The substation was planned based on emergency pandemic response protocols that advise the separation of emergency response teams so that the entire crew is not exposed in the event that one first responder contracts COVID-19. This step will help to ensure continuity of emergency services throughout the COVID-19 pandemic.

Station 121 remains the primary location of the Plain Township Fire Department. Substation 122 at the NAPLS Bus Garage will house a three or four person crew including a lieutenant and firefighter-paramedics cross staffing an engine and medic.

This is another great example of the community‚Äôs intergovernmental cooperation. The Fire Department and Plain Township Officials would like express their gratitude to the School District for helping establish this substation.

WE NEED YOUR HELP!

LESS THAN TWO WEEKS LEFT TO HELP NEW ALBANY EARN $40,000 TOWARD A NEW PLAYGROUND

Download and log into the AEP Ohio It‚Äôs Your Power App with your AEP Ohio account credentials. Search ‚ÄúIt‚Äôs Your Power‚Äù in the app store or go to www.AEPOhio.com/ItsYourPower to download the app. Once you download the app, order the It‚Äôs Your Power smart thermostat and bridge to maximize the app and gain additional points toward our community goal.

To keep saving, take the Online Energy Profile through the app or at www.AEPOhio.com/Kit. Answer questions about your energy use to receive recommendations for saving energy and a FREE energy efficiency tool kit. The kit includes LED light bulbs, a night light, weather stripping and insulated switch covers.

New Albany is currently participating in the AEP Ohio Community Energy Savers program, which rewards residents and businesses for reducing energy usage in their community.

post_text: An official Welcome Ground Flourishing Ceremony was held at Google this morning. Construction of the new Google Data Center Campus in New Albany began with the construction of facilities that are outside the New Albany-Plain Local School district boundaries. However, Google has stated that future construction at the Data Center Campus will include buildings located in our school district boundaries. We welcome future educational opportunities and partnerships that will benefit our students. We are also grateful for the future income potential beyond the initial land transfer revenue that we will receive. #NAPride New Albany, Ohio Government

post_text: Congratulations to school resource officer Leland Kelly! #NAPride
shared_text:
New Albany, Ohio Government
October 25, 2019 at 1:02 PM ¬∑

New Albany police officer Leland Kelly was a STAR award recipient at the recent Franklin County Sheriff recognition dinner. The STAR award represents an officer who embodies selflessness, teamwork, accountability and respect. Officer Kelly has volunteered many hours towards children's charities and the Special Olympics. Thanks for your service to the community Officer Kelly!
